# Observability & Logging

- Log **JSON to stdout** only. Never write plain-text or file logs.
- Use `pkg/logger` (ECS-style fields). Get the request logger from context:

```go
logger.From(ctx).Info("user_created", slog.String("user_id", id))
```

- Always include `request_id` (and `trace_id` when available) — `httpx.AccessLog`
  adds `request_id` automatically.
- Propagate `traceparent` (W3C Trace Context) on every outbound call.
- Expose `/metrics`; follow `platform-contracts/docs/metrics.md` naming. Keep
  label cardinality bounded (no raw ids in labels).
- Instrument with the OpenTelemetry SDK; export OTLP to the collector.
